      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i get the \"both sides\" thing but i'm asking for a bit more depth. if we look at the actual data, doesn't the consensus among most major economists show that tariffs are basically just a tax on the public that fails to actually help the workers in the long run? feels like one side is just backed by facts while the other is just political posturing.",
